<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870922-0094 </DOCNO><HL> Grumman Unit WinsNavy Aircraft WorkTotaling $138.7 Million</HL><DD> 09/22/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GQ GM GMH ALD TGT RTN CMIC SSSSAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Grumman Aerospace Corp., a unit of Grumman Corp., won Navy contracts totaling $138.7 million for E-2C aircraft production and EA-6B aircraft parts.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a subsidiary of General Motors Corp., received contracts totaling $120.2 million for torpedo test and support equipment and Phoenix missile services for the Navy and TOW-2 missiles for the Army.    Units of Allied-Signal Inc. got contracts totaling $73.1 million for F-15 aircraft test equipment for the Air Force, chemical agent monitoring equipment for the Army and FA-18 aircraft equipment for the Navy.    California Microwave Inc. won a $21.6 million Army contract for classified services.    Newport News Shipbuilding andamp; Dry Dock Co., a unit of Tenneco Inc., was issued a $16.8 million Navy contract for submarine construction materials.    Big Three Industries was awarded a $15 million Air Force contract for gaseous nitrogen for space shuttle missions.    Stewart andamp; Stevenson Services Inc. won a $12.7 million contract to provide power-generating equipment for three cruisers being built for the Navy.    Raytheon Co. received a $10.7 million Army contract for electronic equipment. </TEXT></DOC>